    "summary": "As Project Management Officer at the National Institute for Public Health and the Environment (RIVM), I contribute to projects on promoting healthy living environments on a national and EU level; the H2020 Exposome project Equal-Life (www.equal-life.eu/en) and i-GLO (www.gezondeleefomgeving.nl/).\n\nMy interdisciplinary background, analytical and social skills make that I am 'the generalist' that aims to translate knowledge in a way that resonates with the end user. I use my experience in knowledge brokering, communications and interdisciplinary research to optimize knowledge use for policy that promotes healthy (living) environments.\n\nI like to innovate, connect and communicate. My fields of interest are: (public) health, sustainability & the environment, climate adaptation, biomedical sciences, people & culture.",
